In March 2008, the FASB issued SFAS No. 161 (SFAS 161), . SFAS 161 amends and expands the disclosure requirements of SFAS No. 133, . It requires qualitative disclosures about objectives and strategies for using derivatives, quantitative disclosures about fair value amounts of gains and losses on derivative instruments, and disclosures about credit-risk-related contingent features in derivative agreements. This statement is effective for fiscal periods beginning after November 15, 2008. The Company is currently evaluating the impact of SFAS 161 on the consolidated financial statements.
